links.title: Social Media Giants - Operating Margin
links.description: Operating margins of Facebook and Alphabet have been consistent since 2014 Revenues from advertising in 2019 formed 98%, 87%, and 84% for Facebook (FB), Twitter (TWTR), and Alphabet (GOOG) respectively. Twitter turned profitable in 2018, but the operating margin has been declining since 2019, before being severely dented by COVID-19.
